 Button once to exit and save settings.<br />4. Inside the Manage Connections, set Mobile Network to on.<br />5. Return to the main screen by pressing End Call and you should see your phone getting signal<br />6. As a reminder, if you ever remove the SIM card from your phone, you will need to set the Network Technology as GSM/UMTS again<br /><span style=""></span><br /><strong><font color="#2763a5">How to Unlock BlackBerry Bold 9900 and 9930</font></strong><br /><ol style=""><li style="">Ensure a SIM Card is inserted</li><li style="">Go to &lsquo;Manage Connections&rsquo;</li><li style="">Click on &lsquo;Turn All Connections Off&rsquo;</li><li style="">Go to &lsquo;Options&rsquo;</li><li style="">Click on &lsquo;Device&rsquo;</li><li style="">Click on &lsquo;Advanced System Settings&rsquo;</li><li style="">Click on &lsquo;SIM Card&rsquo;</li><li style="">Type &lsquo;MEPD&rsquo; (NOTE: you might need to type in caps, also letters will not appear on-screen but you will be presented with personalization screen, that will display 5 locks such as network, service provider etc)</li><li style="">Type &lsquo;MEP2&prime; (make sure to hold ALT for 2) or hold ALT and type MEPE (NOTE: user will be prompted to enter MEP code)</li><li style="">Enter the MEP2 code numbers only (CONFIRM you get &ldquo;Code Accepted&rdquo; message)<ul style=""><li style="">*If you also have a MEP4 code, type &lsquo;MEP4&prime; (you will be prompted to enter MEP code)</li><li style="">Enter the MEP4 code (CONFIRM you get &ldquo;Code Accepted&rdquo; message)</li></ul></li><li style="">Reboot device by pulling battery out</li><li style="">Go to &lsquo;Manage Connections&rsquo;</li><li style="">Click on &lsquo;Restore Connections&rsquo;</li><li style="">Device is now unlocked</li></ol><font color="#2763a5"><strong style="">Verizon phones only</strong>:&nbsp; </font>You might need to remove&nbsp; &ldquo;Activation Required&rdquo; on the screen or change the Phone Number to yours by following steps below